00:08:43,726 --> 00:08:45,926
Rachel, you can't live
your life on pins and needles.

248
00:08:45,961 --> 00:08:47,361
It's not healthy for you.

249
00:08:47,396 --> 00:08:49,441
It's not healthy for Mike.
It's not healthy for anyone.

250
00:08:49,465 --> 00:08:50,642
And forgetting about him
is healthy?

251
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:51,977
Isn't that why
you took this case?

252
00:08:52,001 --> 00:08:53,901
To give yourself
something to focus on?

253
00:08:53,936 --> 00:08:55,102
Yes, but I just--

254
00:08:55,137 --> 00:08:56,403
Then don't fight it.

255
00:08:56,438 --> 00:08:58,272
If working to free
an innocent man helps you

256
00:08:58,307 --> 00:08:59,451
to forget about Mike
for a while,

257
00:08:59,475 --> 00:09:03,377
he would be the first person
to tell you to do it.

258
00:09:03,412 --> 00:09:04,945
And trust me,

259
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:07,848
if you really
lose yourself in this,

260
00:09:07,883 --> 00:09:10,228
I have a feeling it's gonna seem
like a lot less than two years

261
00:09:10,252 --> 00:09:12,419
before he gets out.

262
00:09:12,454 --> 00:09:20,460
<i>♪ ♪</i>

263
00:09:22,765 --> 00:09:23,730
Where's Harvey?

264
00:09:23,766 --> 00:09:24,731
Harvey's not here.

265
00:09:24,767 --> 00:09:25,767
Well, get his ass in here

266
00:09:25,801 --> 00:09:27,212
because he made some
goddamn side deal

267
00:09:27,236 --> 00:09:28,747
with those traders
and I want them out.

268
00:09:28,771 --> 00:09:31,438
Louis, I am telling you,
now is not the time.

269
00:09:31,473 --> 00:09:33,273
And I am telling you
that I cannot look at

270
00:09:33,309 --> 00:09:36,076
their smug, stupid faces
for one more day.

271
00:09:36,111 --> 00:09:37,611
Maybe you don't
have to look at them.

272
00:09:37,646 --> 00:09:38,612
What are you talking about?

273
00:09:38,647 --> 00:09:39,613
Louis, did I ever tell you

274
00:09:39,648 --> 00:09:41,088
about my first apartment
in the city?

275
00:09:41,116 --> 00:09:42,082
No.

276
00:09:42,117 --> 00:09:44,151
I was sharing a 400
square-foot studio

277
00:09:44,186 --> 00:09:46,753
and it was a disaster
until we finally decided

278
00:09:46,789 --> 00:09:48,689
that we had to separate
our spaces for privacy.

279
00:09:48,724 --> 00:09:50,235
Well, this isn't
"The Brady Bunch," Donna.

280
00:09:50,259 --> 00:09:52,370
We can't put a masking tape line
down the center of the office.

281
00:09:52,394 --> 00:09:54,261
I'm not talking about
masking tape, Louis.

282
00:09:54,296 --> 00:09:56,363
I am talking about
hiring an architect

283
00:09:56,398 --> 00:09:59,466
to reconfigure the offices.

284
00:09:59,501 --> 00:10:01,068
[laughing]
You're right!

285
00:10:01,103 --> 00:10:02,881
We can even do a remodel, which
is what I've been wanting to do

286
00:10:02,905 --> 00:10:04,137
for the last five years.

287
00:10:04,173 --> 00:10:05,784
And the best part is,
you don't have to deal with

288
00:10:05,808 --> 00:10:07,574
those asshole traders
ever again.

289
00:10:07,609 --> 00:10:08,575
Donna, you're a genius.

290
00:10:08,610 --> 00:10:09,810
I know.

291
00:10:09,845 --> 00:10:11,256
Get me the names of
six architects before lunch.

292
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,357
Louis, you have
your own secretary.

293
00:10:12,381 --> 00:10:13,347
Thanks for nothing.

294
00:10:13,382 --> 00:10:14,348
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

295
00:10:14,383 --> 00:10:16,049
Why do I even?

296
00:10:20,956 --> 00:10:22,155
Nice of<i> you</i> to show up.

297
00:10:22,191 --> 00:10:24,624
Been peeling these
potatoes by myself.

298
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:27,227
Sorry, I...got caught up.

299
00:10:27,262 --> 00:10:29,463
Speaking of which,
how'd it go with your lawyer?

300
00:10:29,498 --> 00:10:31,331
You gettin' out of here?

301
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,933
What?

302
00:10:32,968 --> 00:10:35,702
I'm just kidding.
So what's going on?

303
00:10:35,738 --> 00:10:37,738
Nothing.

304
00:10:37,773 --> 00:10:38,972
It's not important.

305
00:10:39,008 --> 00:10:40,719
Your lawyer shows up
without you knowing about it

306
00:10:40,743 --> 00:10:41,942
and it's not important?

307
00:10:41,977 --> 00:10:43,221
Come on, do I look like
I was born yesterday?

308
00:10:43,245 --> 00:10:44,211
I just said
it is not important.

309
00:10:44,246 --> 00:10:45,523
And I'm sorry
I left you hanging,

310
00:10:45,547 --> 00:10:47,258
but you wouldn't even
have this job without me.

311
00:10:47,282 --> 00:10:49,349
I wouldn't even need this job
if it weren't for you.

312
00:10:49,385 --> 00:10:51,251
So what's your problem?

313
00:10:51,286 --> 00:10:53,120
I'm sorry, Kevin, I'm...

314
00:10:53,155 --> 00:10:55,088
<i>[tense music]</i>

315
00:10:55,124 --> 00:10:57,324
I'm just not having a good day.

316
00:10:57,359 --> 00:10:58,325
Hey, it's okay.

317
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,493
Don't sweat it.
All right?

318
00:10:59,528 --> 00:11:02,162
I mean, it's none of
my business anyway.

319
00:11:02,197 --> 00:11:04,131
<i>♪ ♪</i>

320
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:07,701
No, actually,
it is your business.

321
00:11:07,736 --> 00:11:09,981
He came here to tell me that he
tried to get Gallo transferred,

322
00:11:10,005 --> 00:11:14,908
but...it's not gonna happen.

323
00:11:14,943 --> 00:11:16,187
Well, as long as
we stick together,

324
00:11:16,211 --> 00:11:19,579
we can deal with Gallo
anyway, right?

325
00:11:19,615 --> 00:11:23,417
Yeah, that's--
that's what I told Harvey.

326
00:11:23,452 --> 00:11:24,651
Right.

327
00:11:24,686 --> 00:11:25,697
Next time you talk to him,

328
00:11:25,721 --> 00:11:27,954
tell him I said
thanks for trying.

329
00:11:27,990 --> 00:11:30,991
<i>♪ ♪</i>

330
00:11:33,328 --> 00:11:34,294
How'd it go?

331
00:11:34,329 --> 00:11:35,762
He said he had
to think about it.

332
00:11:35,798 --> 00:11:37,431
What?
Why?

333
00:11:37,466 --> 00:11:39,533
'Cause he's an idiot,
that's why.

334
00:11:39,568 --> 00:11:40,767
So what're you gonna do?

335
00:11:40,803 --> 00:11:42,569
I'm gonna figure out
how to buy us some time.

336
00:11:42,604 --> 00:11:44,938
Well, you better do it fast
because Cahill's in your office

337
00:11:44,973 --> 00:11:46,640
and he wants an answer.

338
00:11:49,344 --> 00:11:50,510
Sean.

339
00:11:50,546 --> 00:11:51,778
What'd he say?

340
00:11:51,814 --> 00:11:53,914
Said he wants to see
the details in writing.

341
00:11:53,949 --> 00:11:55,026
I'm not in the mood, Harvey.

342
00:11:55,050 --> 00:11:56,383
And I'm not messing around.

343
00:11:56,418 --> 00:11:58,351
Please tell me
you're kidding me.

344
00:11:58,387 --> 00:11:59,397
Oh, come on, this is bullshit.

345
00:11:59,421 --> 00:12:00,387
You know my word is good.

346
00:12:00,422 --> 00:12:01,721
Yeah, and I told him that,

348
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:05,325
and then find out
commuting his sentence

349
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,793
really means cutting it in half.

350
00:12:06,829 --> 00:12:07,894
He's not risking anything.

351
00:12:07,930 --> 00:12:09,229
No one's gonna find out.

352
00:12:09,264 --> 00:12:11,631
I'm sure that's exactly
what Frank Gallo thought.

353
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:14,534
So either put it in writing
or we don't have a deal.

354
00:12:16,171 --> 00:12:18,071
He didn't go for it, did he?

355
00:12:18,107 --> 00:12:19,117
What are you talking about?

356
00:12:19,141 --> 00:12:20,774
Mike being at risk
has nothing to do

357
00:12:20,809 --> 00:12:21,953
with putting anything
in writing.

358
00:12:21,977 --> 00:12:23,121
And you told me
he wouldn't go for it,

359
00:12:23,145 --> 00:12:27,447
so Harvey...
tell me the truth.

360
00:12:27,483 --> 00:12:29,049
All right, he said no.

361
00:12:29,084 --> 00:12:30,984
But Sean, I'm telling you,
he'll come around.

362
00:12:31,019 --> 00:12:32,097
He just needs a couple of days.

363
00:12:32,121 --> 00:12:33,561
Do you know how many
strings I pulled

364
00:12:33,589 --> 00:12:34,821
to put this thing in motion?

366
00:12:36,892 --> 00:12:38,458
if this case
wasn't huge for you.

367
00:12:38,494 --> 00:12:39,659
So instead of yelling at me

368
00:12:39,695 --> 00:12:41,072
for saying that it's gonna
take a couple days,

369
00:12:41,096 --> 00:12:43,263
why don't you just
give me a couple of days?

370
00:12:43,298 --> 00:12:44,264
Okay, Harvey.

371
00:12:44,299 --> 00:12:45,632
The deal's still on the table.

372
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:47,712
But if I find a way to move
forward without his help,

373
00:12:47,736 --> 00:12:49,970
there is no deal and
he does the whole two years.

374
00:12:50,005 --> 00:12:52,973
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

375
00:12:53,008 --> 00:12:54,641
<i>♪ ♪</i>

376
00:12:59,911 --> 00:13:02,780
<i>[rousing music]</i>

377
00:13:02,815 --> 00:13:06,250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

378
00:13:06,286 --> 00:13:07,251
Jessica.

379
00:13:07,287 --> 00:13:08,252
Harvey.

380
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:09,587
What's going on with Mike?

381
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:11,989
I gave him Cahill's offer.

382
00:13:12,025 --> 00:13:13,102
And he's thinking about it?

383
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:14,225
I'm working on it.

384
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:15,604
Well, in the meantime,
while you were out,

385
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:17,361
I got a call from Nathan Byrnes.

386
00:13:17,397 --> 00:13:19,308
He thinks someone's trying
to take over his company.

387
00:13:19,332 --> 00:13:20,376
Why the hell would
he think of that?

388
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,632
Because word on the street is,

389
00:13:21,668 --> 00:13:23,178
someone's selling off
a block of his stock.

390
00:13:23,202 --> 00:13:24,302
That doesn't make sense.

391
00:13:24,337 --> 00:13:26,804
We bought Sutter's shares
from him.

392
00:13:27,874 --> 00:13:28,839
Those goddamn traders.

393
00:13:28,875 --> 00:13:29,940
No way.

394
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:31,186
They wouldn't do that
without telling me.

395
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:32,410
They bought it in good faith.

396
00:13:32,445 --> 00:13:34,512
Well, they're dumping it
in bad faith.

397
00:13:35,915 --> 00:13:37,448
- I'll take care of it--
- No.

398
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:39,850
You have your hands
full with Mike.

399
00:13:39,886 --> 00:13:41,018
I can handle this.

400
00:13:41,054 --> 00:13:43,254
Jessica, it was my idea
to involve them.

401
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:44,500
I should be the one
to take care of it.

402
00:13:44,524 --> 00:13:46,357
I don't care whose idea
it was, Harvey.

403
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:48,059
You take care of Mike.

404
00:13:48,094 --> 00:13:55,599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

405
00:13:56,602 --> 00:13:59,603
[phone ringing]

406
00:14:01,441 --> 00:14:02,773
Hello?

407
00:14:02,809 --> 00:14:05,109
<i>You have a call from</i>
<i>Danbury Federal Prison.</i>

408
00:14:05,144 --> 00:14:06,610
<i>Do you accept the charges?</i>

409
00:14:06,646 --> 00:14:08,412
Yes, of course.

410
00:14:08,448 --> 00:14:10,981
<i>[line clicks]</i>
<i>Mike, is everything okay?</i>

411
00:14:11,017 --> 00:14:12,616
Yeah.
Yeah, everything's fine.

412
00:14:12,652 --> 00:14:14,352
I was just thinking about you.

413
00:14:14,387 --> 00:14:15,531
I was thinking about you too.

414
00:14:15,555 --> 00:14:16,721
<i>You were?</i>

415
00:14:16,756 --> 00:14:19,557
<i>Yes, in fact,</i>
<i>I was just in the middle</i>

416
00:14:19,592 --> 00:14:21,459
of a heated discussion with you

417
00:14:21,494 --> 00:14:24,462
about the best way to handle
a death row appeal.

418
00:14:24,497 --> 00:14:25,696
I don't understand.

419
00:14:25,732 --> 00:14:27,498
<i>I took on</i>
<i>an Innocence Project case,</i>

420
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:29,778
just to have something to take
my mind off of our troubles.

421
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:33,971
But I...I didn't want to
take my mind off of you.

422
00:14:34,006 --> 00:14:35,539
<i>So I figured I would just</i>

423
00:14:35,575 --> 00:14:37,641
<i>imagine we were working</i>
<i>on it together.</i>

424
00:14:37,677 --> 00:14:39,677
I don't know what to say.

425
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:42,313
<i>Say you're in.</i>

426
00:14:42,348 --> 00:14:44,648
I mean, that depends on
what strategy we landed on.

427
00:14:44,684 --> 00:14:45,750
<i>Mike, seriously,</i>

428
00:14:45,785 --> 00:14:47,251
is there something wrong?

429
00:14:47,286 --> 00:14:50,388
<i>No, I just wanted to make</i>
<i>sure you were doing okay.</i>

430
00:14:50,423 --> 00:14:53,824
And that...
that we were still good.

431
00:14:53,860 --> 00:14:56,861
<i>Now that I have something to</i>
<i>take my mind off our situation</i>

432
00:14:56,896 --> 00:15:00,297
and connect me to you
at the same time,

433
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:03,934
yeah, we're better than good.

434
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:07,805
<i>[solemn music]</i>

435
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,541
All right, can you do me a
favor and transfer me to Donna?

436
00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:11,642
Of course.

437
00:15:11,677 --> 00:15:12,910
Can I ask why?

438
00:15:12,945 --> 00:15:14,512
<i>I only get one phone call,</i>

439
00:15:14,547 --> 00:15:15,824
and I'm pretty sure
she had something to do

440
00:15:15,848 --> 00:15:19,650
with the idea of you
imagining us working together,

441
00:15:19,685 --> 00:15:21,419
so I just want to thank her.

442
00:15:21,454 --> 00:15:22,520
<i>Okay.</i>

443
00:15:22,555 --> 00:15:23,721
I love you.

444
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:25,055
<i>I love you too.</i>

445
00:15:25,091 --> 00:15:27,124
<i>♪ ♪</i>

446
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:29,093
[phone ringing]

447
00:15:29,128 --> 00:15:30,261
Hello?

448
00:15:30,296 --> 00:15:31,996
<i>Donna, I have Mike</i>
<i>on the phone.</i>

449
00:15:32,031 --> 00:15:34,231
Put him through.

450
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:35,267
Hello?
<i>Donna.</i>

451
00:15:35,301 --> 00:15:36,700
If Harvey's there,
do me a favor--

452
00:15:36,736 --> 00:15:38,580
keep your voice down,
and don't tell him it's me.

453
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:39,637
Mike, what's going on?

454
00:15:39,672 --> 00:15:41,505
I'm not taking the deal,
Donna.

455
00:15:41,541 --> 00:15:42,506
Are you crazy?

456
00:15:42,542 --> 00:15:43,974
<i>It's not that simple.</i>

457
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:45,721
What's not simple about it?
Harvey said that if you--

458
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:46,944
<i>I don't care</i>
<i>what Harvey said.</i>

459
00:15:46,979 --> 00:15:48,279
Because what he didn't say

460
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:50,448
is that if I do what he wants
and someone finds out,

461
00:15:50,483 --> 00:15:51,960
then I may never get back
to Rachel at all.

462
00:15:51,984 --> 00:15:53,462
<i>Harvey would never</i>
<i>let them find out--</i>

463
00:15:53,486 --> 00:15:55,130
Donna, look, I called you
so that I didn't want to have

464
00:15:55,154 --> 00:15:56,120
this argument with him.

465
00:15:56,155 --> 00:15:58,022
Now, I don't have much time.

466
00:15:58,057 --> 00:16:00,524
Are you gonna do this for me
or not?

467
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:02,026
I'll tell him.

468
00:16:02,061 --> 00:16:03,839
<i>Then I also need you to</i>
<i>tell him something else for me.</i>

469
00:16:03,863 --> 00:16:06,664
If he comes here to try
to change my mind,

470
00:16:06,699 --> 00:16:08,933
I'm not gonna see him.

471
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:11,936
<i>[dial tone droning]</i>

472
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:15,005
<i>♪ ♪</i>

473
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:16,507
You mind telling me
who the hell said

474
00:16:16,542 --> 00:16:19,043
you can dump Nathan Byrnes'
stock without talking to us?

475
00:16:19,078 --> 00:16:20,255
I don't know what
you're talking about.

476
00:16:20,279 --> 00:16:21,378
Who's Nathan Byrnes?

477
00:16:21,414 --> 00:16:23,113
CEO of Exodyne.

478
00:16:23,149 --> 00:16:24,315
Oh, that Nathan Byrnes.

479
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:26,283
In that case,<i> I</i> said
I could sell that stock

480
00:16:26,319 --> 00:16:27,551
because I own it.

481
00:16:27,587 --> 00:16:31,422
Just like I own this one
and this one and this one.

482
00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:33,457
Hey, look at that,
my Neubacher Capital position's

483
00:16:33,493 --> 00:16:34,925
going through the roof.

484
00:16:34,961 --> 00:16:36,705
That's not the deal you made
with Harvey and you know it.

485
00:16:36,729 --> 00:16:38,796
Welcome to the big,
bad world of Wall Street.

486
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:40,809
Now, do you want something
or can I get back to work?

487
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,233
Oh, I want something.

488
00:16:42,268 --> 00:16:44,379
You're going to unwind that sale
and buy those shares back.

489
00:16:44,403 --> 00:16:46,237
At a premium?
Not gonna happen.

490
00:16:46,272 --> 00:16:47,238
I'm your landlord.

491
00:16:47,273 --> 00:16:48,417
And the fact
you had to lease to me

492
00:16:48,441 --> 00:16:50,018
means you don't have
much of an operation.

493
00:16:50,042 --> 00:16:51,642
You listen to me,
you little pissant.

494
00:16:51,677 --> 00:16:52,821
You don't know who
you're messing with.

495
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,311
Then why don't I find out?

496
00:16:54,347 --> 00:16:55,779
Over dinner?

497
00:16:55,815 --> 00:16:57,414
You've got to be kidding me.

498
00:16:57,450 --> 00:16:59,350
You want me to have
dinner with you

499
00:16:59,385 --> 00:17:01,185
in exchange for
backing off that trade?

