528
00:17:58,811 --> 00:17:59,811
Then get me Rachel.

529
00:17:59,845 --> 00:18:02,046
No, no, Harvey,
you cannot tell her.

530
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:03,113
Like hell I can't.

531
00:18:03,149 --> 00:18:04,693
She's the only one
who can convince him.

532
00:18:04,717 --> 00:18:06,684
If you tell her that
Mike's not taking a deal

533
00:18:06,719 --> 00:18:08,519
that can get him out,
it'll tear her apart.

534
00:18:08,554 --> 00:18:10,454
And if I don't tell her,
he's gonna be in there

535
00:18:10,489 --> 00:18:11,455
for two more years.

536
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:12,456
Is that what she wants?

537
00:18:12,491 --> 00:18:13,457
That's between them.

538
00:18:13,492 --> 00:18:14,458
That's why I want to tell her.

539
00:18:14,493 --> 00:18:15,459
She'll make it between them.

540
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:17,161
- Harvey.
- [scoffs]

541
00:18:17,196 --> 00:18:19,396
God damn it, he plays checkers
with this guy

542
00:18:19,432 --> 00:18:20,509
and thinks he owes him his life.

543
00:18:20,533 --> 00:18:22,232
No, that's not fair
and you know it,

544
00:18:22,268 --> 00:18:25,069
because Mike's loyalty is
the reason you're not in prison.

545
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,604
<i>♪ ♪</i>

546
00:18:26,639 --> 00:18:29,807
That's what's killing me,
Donna, don't you understand?

547
00:18:29,842 --> 00:18:35,179
He's in there instead of me
with a guy I put away,

548
00:18:35,214 --> 00:18:37,748
and I can't just sit here
doing nothing

549
00:18:37,783 --> 00:18:39,984
when he has a chance to get out.

550
00:18:40,019 --> 00:18:42,519
Which is why you have to
think of something else.

551
00:18:42,555 --> 00:18:44,154
Because if you tell
Rachel about this,

552
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:47,491
the life that's waiting
for Mike when he gets out...

553
00:18:47,526 --> 00:18:49,593
it isn't going to be there.

554
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:55,633
<i>♪ ♪</i>

555
00:18:57,903 --> 00:19:00,504
Harvey. I'm surprised
to see you here so soon.

556
00:19:00,539 --> 00:19:02,084
I didn't think
you'd turn him this fast.

557
00:19:02,108 --> 00:19:03,073
I need more time.

558
00:19:03,109 --> 00:19:04,508
I don't think you understand.

559
00:19:04,543 --> 00:19:06,421
I'm being pressured to move
to another investigation.

560
00:19:06,445 --> 00:19:09,179
You've got 24 hours to change
his mind or this thing is done.

561
00:19:09,215 --> 00:19:10,726
Then I need you to
do something for me.

562
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:11,893
I am doing something for you.

563
00:19:11,917 --> 00:19:13,283
I'm getting Mike out of prison.

564
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:15,352
Well, you need to do
something else for me

565
00:19:15,388 --> 00:19:17,721
or that's never gonna happen.

566
00:19:17,757 --> 00:19:19,523
What are you talking about?

567
00:19:19,558 --> 00:19:21,258
I need you to get
into a room with him

568
00:19:21,293 --> 00:19:23,494
because he won't listen
to what I have to say.

569
00:19:23,529 --> 00:19:25,040
What exactly do you
want me to tell him

570
00:19:25,064 --> 00:19:26,196
that you haven't already?

571
00:19:26,232 --> 00:19:27,665
Sean, Mike's a bleeding heart.

572
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:29,566
You need to make the case
directly to him.

573
00:19:29,602 --> 00:19:32,202
He needs to see the victims of
whatever the hell this guy did.

574
00:19:32,238 --> 00:19:33,604
That's a swell idea, Harvey,

575
00:19:33,639 --> 00:19:35,673
but if I go into that prison
and someone sees me,

576
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:37,041
not only are we dead
in the water,

577
00:19:37,076 --> 00:19:38,642
but Mike's life
isn't worth shit.

578
00:19:38,678 --> 00:19:39,755
You think I don't know that?

579
00:19:39,779 --> 00:19:41,289
What the hell do you think
I'm doing here?

580
00:19:41,313 --> 00:19:42,391
What are you talking about?

581
00:19:42,415 --> 00:19:43,380
I have a plan.

582
00:19:43,416 --> 00:19:44,648
But you're not gonna like it.

583
00:19:44,684 --> 00:19:45,716
Why not?

584
00:19:45,751 --> 00:19:47,229
Because I need you
to pull another string,

585
00:19:47,253 --> 00:19:49,386
and I need you to do it
before Frank Gallo tries

586
00:19:49,422 --> 00:19:51,155
something else with Mike.

587
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:53,157
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

588
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:56,193
[crowd chatter]

589
00:19:59,665 --> 00:20:00,931
All right, fake lawyer.

590
00:20:00,966 --> 00:20:04,068
Let's see what you got.

591
00:20:04,103 --> 00:20:05,703
You're gonna let me
look into it for you?

592
00:20:05,738 --> 00:20:07,404
Look into it?
Shit.

593
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:09,351
You're gonna get me out of here
like you promised.

594
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:10,340
I never promised.

595
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:11,520
I said there was
an excellent chance

596
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:13,410
that you could get--
Six weeks, brother.

597
00:20:13,446 --> 00:20:16,413
I'll be counting the days.

598
00:20:16,449 --> 00:20:18,415
I'll file the motion
first thing in the morning.

599
00:20:18,451 --> 00:20:19,416
There you go.

600
00:20:19,452 --> 00:20:21,418
That's what I'm talking about.

601
00:20:21,454 --> 00:20:24,254
And if I find out you're
screwing me on any level,

602
00:20:24,290 --> 00:20:27,124
you better hole up in some
dark corner of this prison,

603
00:20:27,159 --> 00:20:30,394
pray to God
I don't find your ass.

604
00:20:30,429 --> 00:20:37,167
<i>♪ ♪</i>

605
00:20:37,203 --> 00:20:39,269
What was that all about?

606
00:20:40,806 --> 00:20:44,108
Looks like he took me up
on my offer after all.

607
00:20:44,143 --> 00:20:48,712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

608
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,605
God damn it, Gretchen,
where the hell is she?

609
00:20:58,629 --> 00:20:59,762
Where the hell is who?

610
00:20:59,797 --> 00:21:01,375
That architect
you were supposed to call.

611
00:21:01,399 --> 00:21:03,439
She's not supposed to be here
for another half hour.

612
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:05,067
And if I want
someone's business,

613
00:21:05,102 --> 00:21:07,203
I show up a half-hour
early at the latest.

614
00:21:07,238 --> 00:21:08,982
And what exactly are
you looking to have me do

615
00:21:09,006 --> 00:21:10,139
about your little conundrum?

616
00:21:10,174 --> 00:21:11,607
I want you to give her a call

617
00:21:11,642 --> 00:21:13,854
and tell her if she doesn't have
the goddamn common courtesy

618
00:21:13,878 --> 00:21:15,989
to show up early, then she might
as well not show up at all.

619
00:21:16,013 --> 00:21:17,880
- Mr. Litt.
- I--

620
00:21:17,915 --> 00:21:19,348
Y-yes?

621
00:21:19,383 --> 00:21:20,549
I'm Tara Messer.

622
00:21:20,585 --> 00:21:22,117
I'm here to discuss
your remodel needs.

623
00:21:22,153 --> 00:21:23,519
My needs?

624
00:21:23,554 --> 00:21:26,088
Well, I'm sorry, Ms.
Was-Going-to-Be-Our-Architect.

625
00:21:26,123 --> 00:21:27,301
We no longer need your service.

626
00:21:27,325 --> 00:21:28,457
Gretchen, calm down.

627
00:21:28,492 --> 00:21:30,292
You are overreacting
like a crazy woman.

628
00:21:30,328 --> 00:21:31,360
You're hired.

629
00:21:31,395 --> 00:21:32,395
I am?

630
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:33,929
Oh, yeah.
You're right for the job.

631
00:21:33,965 --> 00:21:34,930
I can feel it.

632
00:21:34,966 --> 00:21:36,765
Oh, you can feel something,
all right.

633
00:21:36,801 --> 00:21:38,841
Then why don't we start
with what you're looking for

634
00:21:38,869 --> 00:21:40,903
in the space?

635
00:21:40,938 --> 00:21:42,638
Oh.
Space.

636
00:21:42,673 --> 00:21:44,440
Right, the space.
Exactly.

637
00:21:44,475 --> 00:21:47,209
What I'm looking for are clear
yet unobtrusive boundaries

638
00:21:47,245 --> 00:21:48,744
between our offices
and the tenants'.

639
00:21:48,779 --> 00:21:51,513
But it needs to be
elegant and organic

640
00:21:51,549 --> 00:21:53,249
or we might as well
not do it at all.

641
00:21:53,284 --> 00:21:54,483
I understand.

642
00:21:54,518 --> 00:21:58,120
Like the perfect aria
leading seamlessly

643
00:21:58,155 --> 00:22:00,189
to its inevitable cadenza.

644
00:22:00,224 --> 00:22:01,224
You're an opera lover?

645
00:22:01,259 --> 00:22:02,391
Second only to the ballet.

646
00:22:02,426 --> 00:22:03,993
Then I suggest we start
with a marriage.

647
00:22:04,028 --> 00:22:05,861
I mean a tour.

648
00:22:05,896 --> 00:22:08,897
<i>♪ ♪</i>

649
00:22:15,106 --> 00:22:16,272
Excuse me, Professor Dunbar.

650
00:22:16,307 --> 00:22:17,406
Do you have a moment?

651
00:22:17,441 --> 00:22:18,974
This is the faculty lounge,
Ms. Zane.

652
00:22:19,010 --> 00:22:20,020
You're not supposed
to be in here.

653
00:22:20,044 --> 00:22:21,543
I understand that,
and I'm sorry.

654
00:22:21,579 --> 00:22:25,047
It's just this is important
and you weren't in your office.

655
00:22:25,082 --> 00:22:26,148
What can I do for you?

656
00:22:26,183 --> 00:22:28,417
I met with
Leonard Bailey yesterday.

657
00:22:28,452 --> 00:22:29,796
He's the inmate on death--
I know who he is.

658
00:22:29,820 --> 00:22:31,720
Is there a problem?
Yes, there is.

659
00:22:31,756 --> 00:22:35,057
He's rotting on death row for
a crime that he didn't commit.

660
00:22:35,092 --> 00:22:37,159
So you met with him
for ten minutes

661
00:22:37,194 --> 00:22:38,472
and you're ready to release him?

662
00:22:38,496 --> 00:22:39,628
No, what I'm saying is--

663
00:22:39,664 --> 00:22:41,264
You're a second-year
law student, Rachel.

664
00:22:41,299 --> 00:22:42,542
I asked you to be a part of this

665
00:22:42,566 --> 00:22:43,944
because you're one of
my brightest students,

666
00:22:43,968 --> 00:22:45,301
but I also asked
you in particular

667
00:22:45,336 --> 00:22:48,370
because I didn't think
you'd be so naive.

668
00:22:48,406 --> 00:22:49,638
Excuse me?

669
00:22:49,674 --> 00:22:51,473
Your job wasn't to
talk to Mr. Bailey once

670
00:22:51,509 --> 00:22:53,609
and, after being moved
by his tale of woe,

671
00:22:53,644 --> 00:22:55,577
tell me to jump him
to the top of the pile.

672
00:22:55,613 --> 00:22:57,846
It was to assess his case
and present evidence.

673
00:22:57,882 --> 00:22:59,715
And that's exactly
what I'm doing here.

674
00:22:59,750 --> 00:23:01,016
I just left two boxes

675
00:23:01,052 --> 00:23:04,286
of textbook prosecutorial
misconduct with your secretary.

676
00:23:04,322 --> 00:23:06,588
You found all of that
since yesterday?

677
00:23:06,624 --> 00:23:09,491
Yes, because while I may only
be a second-year law student,

678
00:23:09,527 --> 00:23:11,060
I have been
a practicing paralegal

679
00:23:11,095 --> 00:23:14,163
for the past eight years.

680
00:23:14,198 --> 00:23:16,532
Looks like I have
some reading to do.

681
00:23:16,567 --> 00:23:18,000
<i>[tense music]</i>

682
00:23:18,035 --> 00:23:19,568
I'm sorry for
interrupting your day.

683
00:23:19,603 --> 00:23:21,570
Good afternoon, Ms. Zane.

684
00:23:21,605 --> 00:23:24,139
Good afternoon, Professor.

685
00:23:24,175 --> 00:23:28,110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

686
00:23:28,145 --> 00:23:29,912
And then we use
the glass motif

687
00:23:29,947 --> 00:23:31,947
you already have
to partition their space

688
00:23:31,982 --> 00:23:35,284
from yours starting at
that wall over there.

689
00:23:35,319 --> 00:23:37,653
And no one ever knows
they're two separate entities.

690
00:23:37,688 --> 00:23:39,988
And if we use
the frosted glass,

691
00:23:40,024 --> 00:23:42,257
you'll never even have to
lay eyes on them.

692
00:23:42,293 --> 00:23:44,126
Well, there's
just one more thing.

693
00:23:44,161 --> 00:23:45,794
You want to know
if I can design another

694
00:23:45,830 --> 00:23:47,129
bullpen area for your side.

695
00:23:47,164 --> 00:23:48,975
After all, it's the heart
and soul of the space.

696
00:23:48,999 --> 00:23:50,032
You get that?

697
00:23:50,067 --> 00:23:52,067
It's my job to get that.

698
00:23:52,103 --> 00:23:53,369
I don't understand.

699
00:23:53,404 --> 00:23:56,438
To me, architecture isn't
just about design.

700
00:23:56,474 --> 00:24:00,209
It's--it's about connecting with
my clients on an intimate level.

701
00:24:00,244 --> 00:24:02,144
Well, you're very good at it.

702
00:24:02,179 --> 00:24:04,747
And you know, it's too bad you
already sublet to someone else.

703
00:24:04,782 --> 00:24:06,382
We're looking to
expand ourselves.

704
00:24:06,417 --> 00:24:07,950
This space would
have been perfect.

705
00:24:07,985 --> 00:24:08,951
Are you serious?

706
00:24:08,986 --> 00:24:09,952
Yeah.

707
00:24:09,987 --> 00:24:11,153
In fact, it's so perfect,

708
00:24:11,188 --> 00:24:13,589
