00:24:53,197 --> 00:24:54,163
That's one way
of looking at it.

732
00:24:54,198 --> 00:24:55,164
No, there's another way.

733
00:24:55,199 --> 00:24:56,865
The answer is no.
Okay, fine.

734
00:24:56,901 --> 00:24:58,278
I'll just stick to
the original plan

735
00:24:58,302 --> 00:24:59,780
of having her completely
redesign our space,

736
00:24:59,804 --> 00:25:01,047
and I'll just make sure
it takes long enough

737
00:25:01,071 --> 00:25:02,382
for her to fall madly
in love with me,

738
00:25:02,406 --> 00:25:04,050
and it shouldn't take more
than two or three years.

739
00:25:04,074 --> 00:25:07,042
Louis, I want you to
look at me when I say this.

740
00:25:07,077 --> 00:25:09,711
If you hire this woman
to do anything relating

741
00:25:09,747 --> 00:25:11,180
to this firm's space,

742
00:25:11,215 --> 00:25:13,682
I will personally throw you
off the roof this building.

743
00:25:13,717 --> 00:25:15,284
Is that clear?

744
00:25:15,319 --> 00:25:16,285
So you'll think about it?

745
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:19,188
Get out.

746
00:25:19,223 --> 00:25:20,722
[scoffs]

747
00:25:23,194 --> 00:25:25,694
Yo.
Ahnold.

748
00:25:25,729 --> 00:25:27,362
Come on.
Let's see what you got.

749
00:25:27,398 --> 00:25:29,465
[grunts]
I didn't know you played.

750
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:30,899
Played?
Shit.

751
00:25:30,935 --> 00:25:34,570
I set the P.S. 092
single-game scoring record.

752
00:25:34,605 --> 00:25:37,473
P.S. 092 is an elementary
school, my friend.

753
00:25:37,508 --> 00:25:40,375
Yeah, sixth grade.
I dominated.

754
00:25:40,411 --> 00:25:43,011
Heard you had to file that
motion for Gallo's parole.

755
00:25:43,047 --> 00:25:44,746
- I did.
- Already?

756
00:25:44,782 --> 00:25:46,415
It was an 18-page
sentencing amendment.

757
00:25:46,450 --> 00:25:47,716
I could do that in my sleep.

758
00:25:47,751 --> 00:25:49,518
I should get you to
do some work for me.

759
00:25:49,553 --> 00:25:51,286
Why?
You need some?

760
00:25:51,322 --> 00:25:53,322
No, but if I did,
I'd probably get myself a lawyer

761
00:25:53,357 --> 00:25:54,556
who didn't sleep in a prison.

762
00:25:54,592 --> 00:25:56,458
[chuckles]

763
00:25:56,494 --> 00:25:57,759
[clears throat]

764
00:25:57,795 --> 00:25:58,760
You all right?

765
00:25:58,796 --> 00:25:59,828
[clears throat]

766
00:25:59,864 --> 00:26:01,630
I don't--I don't know.

767
00:26:01,665 --> 00:26:02,742
What do you mean,
you don't know?

768
00:26:02,766 --> 00:26:04,600
- [coughs]
- What is it, your stomach?

769
00:26:04,635 --> 00:26:05,745
Oh, my God,
something's not right.

770
00:26:05,769 --> 00:26:06,735
Take a deep breath.

771
00:26:06,770 --> 00:26:08,136
Put your head down.

772
00:26:08,172 --> 00:26:10,072
Oh, God, I can't--
that's not gonna do anything.

773
00:26:10,107 --> 00:26:11,273
I think...

774
00:26:11,308 --> 00:26:12,519
[echoing]
Oh, my God, I think somebody

775
00:26:12,543 --> 00:26:13,509
did something to me.

776
00:26:13,544 --> 00:26:14,910
Hey, can I get
some help over here?

777
00:26:14,945 --> 00:26:15,911
Guard!

778
00:26:15,946 --> 00:26:17,613
Mike, talk to me.

779
00:26:17,648 --> 00:26:19,114
It's Gallo.

780
00:26:19,149 --> 00:26:20,983
Yeah, he must've put
something in my--

781
00:26:21,018 --> 00:26:23,118
Somebody do something!
Guard!

782
00:26:23,153 --> 00:26:24,319
Call Harvey.

783
00:26:24,355 --> 00:26:25,854
Guard!

784
00:26:25,890 --> 00:26:27,723
Mike.
Mike!

785
00:26:32,585 --> 00:26:35,453
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

786
00:26:35,489 --> 00:26:37,122
<i>♪ ♪</i>

787
00:26:37,157 --> 00:26:38,456
[phone ringing]

788
00:26:38,492 --> 00:26:40,125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

789
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:41,426
Where is he?

790
00:26:41,461 --> 00:26:43,306
If I knew who you were
talking about, maybe I could--

791
00:26:43,330 --> 00:26:44,896
Mike Ross.
I need to see him right now.

792
00:26:44,931 --> 00:26:46,030
And who are you?

793
00:26:46,066 --> 00:26:48,433
Harvey Specter.
I'm his attorney.

794
00:26:48,468 --> 00:26:51,669
<i>♪ ♪</i>

795
00:26:51,705 --> 00:26:54,639
Mr. Ross is in the infirmary,
but you can't see him in there.

796
00:26:54,674 --> 00:26:56,875
Then get me the warden.

797
00:26:56,910 --> 00:26:59,511
<i>♪ ♪</i>

798
00:26:59,546 --> 00:27:01,679
I don't appreciate being
pushed around, Mr. Specter.

799
00:27:01,715 --> 00:27:02,981
I don't care.

800
00:27:03,016 --> 00:27:04,927
I want everyone to know
what happened here today.

801
00:27:04,951 --> 00:27:06,384
They saw what happened.

802
00:27:06,419 --> 00:27:10,088
Yeah, there's a difference
between seeing and knowing.

803
00:27:10,123 --> 00:27:11,389
You Kevin Miller?

804
00:27:11,424 --> 00:27:12,390
Who are you?

805
00:27:12,425 --> 00:27:13,391
Harvey Specter.

806
00:27:13,426 --> 00:27:14,392
I'm Mike Ross's lawyer.

807
00:27:14,427 --> 00:27:15,605
Look, I already
told the warden

808
00:27:15,629 --> 00:27:16,672
I didn't see anyone
touch his food.

809
00:27:16,696 --> 00:27:18,796
Did you see Frank Gallo
with him?

810
00:27:18,832 --> 00:27:19,998
<i>♪ ♪</i>

811
00:27:20,033 --> 00:27:21,132
Did you or didn't you?

812
00:27:21,168 --> 00:27:22,278
Are you trying to
get me killed, man?

813
00:27:22,302 --> 00:27:24,602
Did he touch his food or not?

814
00:27:24,638 --> 00:27:27,172
Yeah, he did,
last night at dinner.

815
00:27:27,207 --> 00:27:28,773
But Mike offered
to get Gallo parole

816
00:27:28,808 --> 00:27:30,853
and Gallo took him up on it,
so why would he poison him?

817
00:27:30,877 --> 00:27:33,178
Because he didn't really
take Mike up on that offer.

818
00:27:33,213 --> 00:27:35,480
He just did it
to get close to him.

819
00:27:35,515 --> 00:27:37,326
Or he did it to give Mike
a taste of what happens

820
00:27:37,350 --> 00:27:38,750
if he doesn't come through.

821
00:27:38,785 --> 00:27:41,386
Either way, you stay the hell
away from that son of a bitch.

822
00:27:41,421 --> 00:27:43,254
All right, that's enough.
Let's go.

823
00:27:43,290 --> 00:27:45,256
<i>♪ ♪</i>

824
00:27:45,292 --> 00:27:46,658
Hey, counselor!

825
00:27:46,693 --> 00:27:49,093
I heard your boy had a little
tummy ache out in the yard.

826
00:27:49,129 --> 00:27:50,094
You piece of shit.

827
00:27:50,130 --> 00:27:51,429
You goddamn poisoned him.

828
00:27:51,464 --> 00:27:52,430
Guards, get him out of here.

829
00:27:52,465 --> 00:27:53,765
I didn't do shit.

830
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:55,311
Why don't you come over here
and say that to my face?

831
00:27:55,335 --> 00:27:56,968
- You think I won't?
- God damn it.

832
00:27:57,003 --> 00:27:59,103
I said get him back to his cell!

833
00:27:59,139 --> 00:28:00,538
Hey, this wasn't part
of the deal.

834
00:28:00,574 --> 00:28:02,140
We talked about you
seeing his roommate,

835
00:28:02,175 --> 00:28:03,541
not rushing Frank Gallo.

836
00:28:03,577 --> 00:28:06,578
Yeah, well, my guy's lying
unconscious in the infirmary.

837
00:28:06,613 --> 00:28:08,913
So sue me.

838
00:28:08,949 --> 00:28:14,552
<i>♪ ♪</i>

839
00:28:14,588 --> 00:28:16,265
How did you know Gallo
would take the bait?

840
00:28:16,289 --> 00:28:18,957
Because he's an animal, and
animals always take the bait.

841
00:28:18,992 --> 00:28:22,060
Well, I'll give you credit for
knowing how it would go down.

842
00:28:22,095 --> 00:28:23,228
I don't need credit.

843
00:28:23,263 --> 00:28:25,029
I need to know
where Mike Ross is.

844
00:28:25,065 --> 00:28:26,831
Where I was instructed
to put him.

845
00:28:26,866 --> 00:28:28,144
Let me tell you something,
Mr. Specter,

846
00:28:28,168 --> 00:28:29,467
I don't know you.

847
00:28:29,502 --> 00:28:30,846
So in case you're thinking
of trying anything,

848
00:28:30,870 --> 00:28:32,148
that kid has a monitor
on his leg,

849
00:28:32,172 --> 00:28:34,205
and if it goes dark
for even one second,

850
00:28:34,241 --> 00:28:36,674
I'm gonna make sure that you
end up in a cell here with him.

851
00:28:36,710 --> 00:28:38,176
It's not gonna go dark,

852
00:28:38,211 --> 00:28:40,178
and he'll be back here
when I said he would.

853
00:28:40,213 --> 00:28:41,613
Then after that,
I'm gonna make sure

854
00:28:41,648 --> 00:28:44,983
he gets out of here.
For good.

855
00:28:45,018 --> 00:28:53,024
<i>♪ ♪</i>

856
00:29:12,245 --> 00:29:14,245
How you feeling?

857
00:29:19,853 --> 00:29:22,186
What's going on?

858
00:29:22,222 --> 00:29:23,621
Where am I?

859
00:29:23,657 --> 00:29:24,822
You're in the back of my car.

860
00:29:24,858 --> 00:29:27,925
You were drugged.

861
00:29:27,961 --> 00:29:28,993
By Gallo.

862
00:29:29,029 --> 00:29:31,629
By me.

863
00:29:31,665 --> 00:29:32,730
What?

864
00:29:32,766 --> 00:29:34,666
Cahill got the warden
and the prison doctor

865
00:29:34,701 --> 00:29:36,034
to put something in your food.

866
00:29:36,069 --> 00:29:37,880
They're the only ones
who know what's going on.

867
00:29:37,904 --> 00:29:39,337
What the hell are
you talking about?

868
00:29:39,372 --> 00:29:41,572
We needed to change your mind
about taking this deal,

869
00:29:41,608 --> 00:29:43,541
and we couldn't do it
as long as you're in there.

870
00:29:43,576 --> 00:29:44,742
Jesus Christ.

871
00:29:44,778 --> 00:29:46,678
So you drugged me?

872
00:29:46,713 --> 00:29:48,913
We needed a cover for why
you're not in your cell,

873
00:29:48,948 --> 00:29:50,226
and this was
the only way to do it.

874
00:29:50,250 --> 00:29:51,516
Are you insane?

875
00:29:51,551 --> 00:29:52,595
You broke me out of prison?

876
00:29:52,619 --> 00:29:54,018
I didn't break
you out of anywhere.

877
00:29:54,054 --> 00:29:55,553
Cahill sanctioned it.

878
00:29:55,588 --> 00:29:58,423
And if anyone's insane,
it's you, 'cause you're the one

879
00:29:58,458 --> 00:30:00,525
turning down a chance
to get out of that place.

880
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:02,538
But we don't have time
to talk about that right now.

881
00:30:02,562 --> 00:30:03,761
Cahill's waiting for us.

882
00:30:03,797 --> 00:30:04,874
You got me out to see Cahill?

883
00:30:04,898 --> 00:30:06,197
I said he's waiting.

884
00:30:06,232 --> 00:30:07,965
I didn't say that's where
I'm taking you.

885
00:30:08,001 --> 00:30:10,968
Well, then where the hell
are you taking me?

886
00:30:13,173 --> 00:30:15,039
[window motor whirrs]

887
00:30:17,711 --> 00:30:20,678
<i>[solemn music]</i>

888
00:30:20,714 --> 00:30:25,083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

889
00:30:25,118 --> 00:30:27,151
You think me spending
a couple of hours with Rachel

890
00:30:27,187 --> 00:30:28,786
is gonna change my mind?

891
00:30:28,822 --> 00:30:32,423
If it doesn't, there's
something wrong with you.

892
00:30:32,459 --> 00:30:34,659
So, you gonna yell at me?

893
00:30:34,694 --> 00:30:36,372
Or you gonna take the only
chance you're gonna get

894
00:30:36,396 --> 00:30:37,740
to be alone with
the woman you love

895
00:30:37,764 --> 00:30:40,331
for the next two years?

896
00:30:40,367 --> 00:30:42,066
Please tell me that
you did not tell her

897
00:30:42,102 --> 00:30:43,234
about Cahill's offer.

898
00:30:43,269 --> 00:30:45,403
Oh, I wanted to.

899
00:30:45,438 --> 00:30:49,140
But you have Donna to thank
for the fact that I didn't.

900
00:30:49,175 --> 00:30:52,877
<i>♪ ♪</i>

901
00:30:52,912 --> 00:30:57,548
What am I supposed to tell
Rachel about why I'm here?

902
00:30:57,584 --> 00:30:59,951
If it were me,
I'd tell her the truth.

903
00:30:59,986 --> 00:31:03,788
Now, since you don't
want to do that,

904
00:31:03,823 --> 00:31:07,091
you're lucky I came up
with something else.

905
00:31:07,127 --> 00:31:10,461
<i>♪ ♪</i>

906
00:31:11,564 --> 00:31:14,265
Wait till it hits 30
and then sell.

907
00:31:15,535 --> 00:31:17,001
Well, look who it is.

908
00:31:17,036 --> 00:31:18,636
You change your mind
about my offer?

909
00:31:18,671 --> 00:31:20,471
[laughs softly]
I'm not there just yet.

910
00:31:20,507 --> 00:31:22,306
But I did come to apologize.

911
00:31:22,342 --> 00:31:24,208
I didn't mean to be
so combative before.

912
00:31:24,244 --> 00:31:27,011
You're a proud woman.
I understand. Bygones.

913
00:31:27,046 --> 00:31:29,614
You know, your operation
here is kind of impressive.

914
00:31:29,649 --> 00:31:31,215
Mind if I look at one?

915
00:31:31,251 --> 00:31:32,795
You can take a look at
anything of mine you want.

916
00:31:32,819 --> 00:31:34,218
[chuckles]

917
00:31:36,022 --> 00:31:37,088
Huh.

918
00:31:37,123 --> 00:31:40,525
Now, what does
that line right there mean?

919
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:42,438
What the hell, that's my
Neubacher Capital position.

920
00:31:42,462 --> 00:31:43,939
Well, it seems to be
falling very quickly.

921
00:31:43,963 --> 00:31:46,464
Is that a good thing?

922
00:31:46,499 --> 00:31:47,465
You did this.

923
00:31:47,500 --> 00:31:48,866
I'm not sure what you mean.

924
00:31:48,902 --> 00:31:49,867
All I did this afternoon

925
00:31:49,903 --> 00:31:51,636
was call my friend
at Jacobson Kearney

926
00:31:51,671 --> 00:31:53,070
and have them issue
a press release

927
00:31:53,106 --> 00:31:55,139
about their client's
merger negotiations.

928
00:31:55,175 --> 00:31:56,819
I mean, how was I supposed
to know that it would make

929
00:31:56,843 --> 00:31:59,343
your Neubacher position
fall through the floor?

930
00:31:59,379 --> 00:32:01,145
You used the information
I gave you yesterday

931
00:32:01,181 --> 00:32:03,247
about my holdings,
that's how.

932
00:32:03,283 --> 00:32:04,894
That's inside information,
and I can prove it.

933
00:32:04,918 --> 00:32:06,217
No, it could have been,

934
00:32:06,252 --> 00:32:08,719
if your attorney hadn't filed
your position with the SEC

935
00:32:08,755 --> 00:32:10,922
ten days earlier than he had to.

936
00:32:10,957 --> 00:32:12,056
I'm not gonna forget this.

937
00:32:12,091 --> 00:32:13,891
Good, because my
operation's been around

938
00:32:13,927 --> 00:32:15,104
a hell of a lot
longer than yours,

939
00:32:15,128 --> 00:32:18,496
and we can be friends
or we can be enemies.

940
00:32:18,531 --> 00:32:19,764
But you mess with me again

941
00:32:19,799 --> 00:32:22,366
and I'll not only kick you
out of these offices,

942
00:32:22,402 --> 00:32:25,570
I'll put you in the ground.

943
00:32:25,605 --> 00:32:28,573
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

944
00:32:28,608 --> 00:32:31,108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

945
00:32:37,083 --> 00:32:38,749
Rachel.

946
00:32:38,785 --> 00:32:40,985
[both gasping]

947
00:32:41,020 --> 00:32:43,988
<i>[solemn music]</i>

948
00:32:44,023 --> 00:32:47,058
<i>♪ ♪</i>

949
00:32:47,093 --> 00:32:48,693
How?

950
00:32:48,728 --> 00:32:50,995
Harvey.

951
00:32:51,030 --> 00:32:53,598
Oh.
I don't understand.

952
00:32:53,633 --> 00:32:55,299
I know you know
about Frank Gallo.

953
00:32:55,335 --> 00:32:56,934
But what you don't know

954
00:32:56,970 --> 00:33:00,104
is that they put me in solitary
confinement for 36 hours.

955
00:33:00,139 --> 00:33:01,572
- Oh, my God.
- It's okay.

956
00:33:01,608 --> 00:33:03,241
I was safe.

957
00:33:03,276 --> 00:33:04,653
Then Harvey made them
watch the video,

958
00:33:04,677 --> 00:33:06,777
which showed that I was
only defending myself.

959
00:33:06,813 --> 00:33:08,424
Turns out they were
more than happy to trade

960
00:33:08,448 --> 00:33:13,117
six hours and an ankle bracelet
to avoid a lawsuit.

961
00:33:13,152 --> 00:33:14,118
<i>♪ ♪</i>

962
00:33:14,153 --> 00:33:16,754
We only have six hours?

963
00:33:16,789 --> 00:33:20,791
Yeah, and I don't want to
waste any of it.

964
00:33:20,827 --> 00:33:28,833
<i>♪ ♪</i>

965
00:33:34,639 --> 00:33:37,474
<i>[tense music]</i>

966
00:33:37,509 --> 00:33:44,614
<i>♪ ♪</i>

967
00:33:44,650 --> 00:33:45,816
Mr. Litt,
what are you--

968
00:33:45,850 --> 00:33:48,317
Oh, please, call me Louis.

969
00:33:48,353 --> 00:33:49,719
What can I do for you, Louis?

970
00:33:49,754 --> 00:33:51,354
Tara, I'm afraid
I have some bad news.

971
00:33:51,389 --> 00:33:52,355
We're not gonna be
moving forward

972
00:33:52,390 --> 00:33:55,158
with the renovations after all.

973
00:33:55,193 --> 00:33:56,292
I'm sorry to hear that.

974
00:33:56,327 --> 00:33:58,027
No, it has nothing
to do with you.

975
00:33:58,062 --> 00:34:00,096
And of course I will pay you
out of my own pocket

976
00:34:00,131 --> 00:34:01,575
for any of the work
you've already done.

977
00:34:01,599 --> 00:34:02,565
That won't be necessary.

978
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:06,135
Please, Tara, I insist.

979
00:34:06,171 --> 00:34:07,904
In that case,
I might as well at least

980
00:34:07,939 --> 00:34:10,072
show you what I had in mind.

981
00:34:12,210 --> 00:34:15,411
As you can see,
these are just rough drawings.

982
00:34:15,446 --> 00:34:16,913
Not to me.

983
00:34:16,948 --> 00:34:20,616
Here's the frosted glass wall
curving in an elegant "S"

984
00:34:20,652 --> 00:34:22,685
that separates the space.

985
00:34:22,720 --> 00:34:23,820
It's beautiful.

986
00:34:23,855 --> 00:34:26,355
That's not even
the best part.

987
00:34:26,391 --> 00:34:28,991
Because I know how important
the new bullpen is to you,

988
00:34:29,027 --> 00:34:32,161
I modeled it after the
Kimmel Center in Philadelphia,

989
00:34:32,197 --> 00:34:33,696
and I enclosed
the entire space--

990
00:34:33,731 --> 00:34:35,598
In mahogany.

991
00:34:35,633 --> 00:34:36,833
[sighs]

992
00:34:36,868 --> 00:34:38,701
It would have been exquisite.

993
00:34:38,736 --> 00:34:41,170
But some things
weren't meant to be.

994
00:34:41,206 --> 00:34:42,738
<i>♪ ♪</i>

995
00:34:42,774 --> 00:34:45,107
Yeah.

996
00:34:45,143 --> 00:34:46,987
How would you feel about
renovating my summer house

997
00:34:47,011 --> 00:34:47,977
in the Hamptons?

998
00:34:48,012 --> 00:34:49,178
I appreciate the thought,

999
00:34:49,214 --> 00:34:50,624
Louis, but I don't do
residential work.

1000
00:34:50,648 --> 00:34:53,282
It's not residential.
I use it as a home office.

1001
00:34:53,318 --> 00:34:54,450
But it would be so small.

1002
00:34:54,485 --> 00:34:55,529
Oh, no, I want
the entire house to be

1003
00:34:55,553 --> 00:34:58,287
a satellite division
of the firm.

1004
00:34:58,323 --> 00:35:00,223
Are you sure?

1005
00:35:00,258 --> 00:35:03,125
I've never been as sure
of anything in my entire life.

1006
00:35:03,161 --> 00:35:05,194
